<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 04 at 2:15PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Gilmer
and east central Murray Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 214 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Conasauga Lake, or 11
miles northeast of Chatsworth. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Chatsworth, Eton, Conasauga Lake, Fort Mountain State Park and
Ramhurst.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
